EURIMBULA RESOURCE RESERVE (MIDDLE ISLAND) â€“ vegetation fire as at 3pm Mon 22 Jun
Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) and Queensland Parks and Wildlife Service (QPWS) crews remain on scene, continuing to monitor a vegetation fire burning within the Eurimbula Resource Reserve. This fire is posing no threat to property at this time. Crews are working to control the blaze and will do so throughout this evening and overnight. Residents may be affected by a smoke haze. People in the area are asked to close windows and doors and if suffering from a respiratory condition, keep medications close by. If residents are concerned their property is under threat, they are advised to call Triple Zero (000) immediately.
